author: Jonathan Tully
title: Report: Fire aboard Royal Caribbean cruise ship
text:
Royal Caribbean cruise officials said a fire broke out on its Freedom of the Seas ship, but it was quickly put out, according to the Orlando Sentinel.
According to the Sentinel, the fire started in a mechanical area as the ship pulled into a Jamaican port, but the ship's fire suppression system extinguished the fire.
Royal Caribbean's Freedom of the Seas ship. USA Today reported passengers were told to go to assembly stations during the incident, a move a Royal Caribbean spokeswoman said was done "out of 'an abundance of caution.'"
The Sentinel reported that all systems are fine aboard Freedom of the Seas, which departed Port Canaveral on a seven-day cruise on Sunday.
Read more at the Orlando Sentinel and USA Today.
